<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1075,1138]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,415,1075,1101]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Description and data:</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Klapalek, F." box="[474,658,1075,1101]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref4895" refString="Klapalek, F. (1912) Plecopteres I. Fam. Perlodidae. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys-Longchamps, 4 (1), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="1912">Klapálek (1912)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, C. F." box="[717,843,1075,1102]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="53 - 87" refId="ref5017" refString="Wu, C. F. (1938) The stoneflies of China (Order Plecoptera). Bulletin of the Peking Society of Natural History, 13 (1), 53 - 87." type="journal article" year="1938">Wu (1938)</bibRefCitation>
. Original illustration (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1163,1075,1101]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1587,1611]" captionTargetBox="[203,1383,1165,1557]" captionTargetId="figure-244@1.[197,1390,1161,1563]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Published illustrations of terminalia of Perlodinella kozlovi (from Wu, 1938)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810225" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810225/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and 
<typeStatus box="[1233,1281,1076,1102]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">type</typeStatus>
series of this species (
<figureCitation box="[247,354,1111,1137]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,812,836]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,250,1991,2015]" captionTargetBox-0="[158,1429,241,785]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1426,902,1962]" captionTargetId-0="figure-39@2.[154,1434,237,789]" captionTargetId-1="figure-84@2.[154,1434,896,1967]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Type series of Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912. A: dried specimens (2 males, 2 females) deposited in NMP – the first male with the “Cotype” label is designated as lectotype; B: collecting labels of the lectotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912, male terminalia.A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: everted epiproct." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810227" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810231" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6810227/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6810231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
) are shown below.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810225" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6810225" box="[151,1067,1587,1611]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810225/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" startId="1.[151,250,1587,1611]" targetBox="[203,1383,1165,1557]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1067,1587,1611]" box="[151,1067,1587,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1587,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Published illustrations of terminalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Klapalek" authorityYear="1912" box="[678,883,1587,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Perlodinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kozlovi">
<emphasis box="[678,883,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Perlodinella kozlovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, C. F." box="[952,1055,1587,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="53 - 87" refId="ref5017" refString="Wu, C. F. (1938) The stoneflies of China (Order Plecoptera). Bulletin of the Peking Society of Natural History, 13 (1), 53 - 87." type="journal article" year="1938">Wu, 1938</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1657,2044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,535,1657,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Supplementary description:</emphasis>
Male and female macropterous. General body color black, except ventral head and sides of female abdomen yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[611,681,1693,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,766,790]" captionTargetBox="[200,1382,191,738]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[191,1396,181,742]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male and female habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Yellow spots present between the hind ocelli and median occiput, sometimes also on clypeus (at least four patterns in male and two patterns in female, see 
<figureCitation box="[1194,1275,1729,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1261,1285]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,820,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-51@3.[167,1421,815,1238]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 5. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male. A–D: head and pronotum with variable color patterns. The positions of variation are marked with red arrows." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810235/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1290,1306,1729,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="5.[151,250,637,661]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,185,609]" captionTargetId="figure-30@5.[151,1436,181,613]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 9. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, female. A–B: head and pronotum with different color patterns, the positions of variation are marked with red arrows; C–D: variability of subgential plates, the outlines are marked in red." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810247/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">9</figureCitation>
). Antennae are brown, palpi dark brown. Pronotum with a yellow median band. Wings brown, veins dark brown, sometimes slightly asymmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[408,477,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[175,1411,1351,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-86@3.[168,1419,1346,1952]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 6. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, left and right wings of the same male, veins asymmetrical. Differences in wing cells are marked in red." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810239/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Legs and cerci mostly dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1657,2044]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="380" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,1837,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Male:</emphasis>
Terga 8–9 slightly sclerotized medially. Median hairs on tergum 8 thick and long. Tergum 9 bearing two sparse patches of sensilla, and a pair of small, sclerotized dots near the lateral margin. Tergum 10 sclerotized, caudally constricted and extended upwards, bearing multiple sensilla basiconica of similar size. Paraprocts divided into a basal sclerite and a subtriangular, eversible apical membrane covered with fine spines. Apical half of the sclerite slender, fingerlike, and straight, with a hook at tip (
<figureCitation box="[732,811,1981,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1991,2015]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,902,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-84@2.[154,1434,896,1967]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912, male terminalia.A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: everted epiproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810231" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810231/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[825,870,1981,2007]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 7" captionStart-1="FIGURE 8" captionStartId-0="4.[151,250,719,743]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox-0="[169,1427,188,689]" captionTargetBox-1="[158,1430,808,1922]" captionTargetId-0="figure-20@4.[153,1434,181,695]" captionTargetId-1="figure-48@4.[154,1434,804,1925]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 7. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male terminalia.A: dorsal; B: ventral; C: terga 9 and 10." captionText-1="FIGURE 8. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male terminalia.A: paraprocts, caudal view; B: everted epiproct, dorsal view; C: everted epiproct and penis, lateral view; D: penis, dorsal view; E: penis, ventral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810241" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810243" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6810241/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6810243/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">7–8</figureCitation>
). Epiproct membranous, with small, round, dorsal process on apex; ventral surface with asperities in a patch (
<figureCitation box="[805,925,2017,2043]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,808,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-48@4.[154,1434,804,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 8. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male terminalia.A: paraprocts, caudal view; B: everted epiproct, dorsal view; C: everted epiproct and penis, lateral view; D: penis, dorsal view; E: penis, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810243/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 8B–C</figureCitation>
). Penis membranous, base with a pair of short arms bearing fine cuticular asperities; median part swelling and bearing larger asperities; apex bilobate, smooth on surface (
<figureCitation box="[247,368,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,808,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-48@4.[154,1434,804,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 8. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male terminalia.A: paraprocts, caudal view; B: everted epiproct, dorsal view; C: everted epiproct and penis, lateral view; D: penis, dorsal view; E: penis, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810243/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="380">Fig. 8C–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810227" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6810227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810227/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="380" startId="2.[151,250,812,836]" targetBox="[158,1429,241,785]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,812,872]" pageId="2" pageNumber="380">
