<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1533,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,296,1534,1560]" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Female:</emphasis>
Coloration similar to males (
<figureCitation box="[631,712,1533,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,812,836]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,241,785]" captionTargetId="figure-39@2.[154,1434,237,789]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Type series of Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912. A: dried specimens (2 males, 2 females) deposited in NMP – the first male with the “Cotype” label is designated as lectotype; B: collecting labels of the lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810227/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[725,742,1534,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,766,790]" captionTargetBox="[200,1382,191,738]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[191,1396,181,742]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, male and female habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810233/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">4</figureCitation>
). There are two morphs of female subgenital plates, with the posterior margin either truncate (
<figureCitation box="[520,606,1569,1596]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="5.[151,250,637,661]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,185,609]" captionTargetId="figure-30@5.[151,1436,181,613]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 9. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, female. A–B: head and pronotum with different color patterns, the positions of variation are marked with red arrows; C–D: variability of subgential plates, the outlines are marked in red." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810247/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
) or M-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[779,869,1569,1596]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="5.[151,250,637,661]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,185,609]" captionTargetId="figure-30@5.[151,1436,181,613]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 9. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, female. A–B: head and pronotum with different color patterns, the positions of variation are marked with red arrows; C–D: variability of subgential plates, the outlines are marked in red." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810247/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1533,2028]" box="[199,422,1605,1632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1606,1632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Nymph:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1533,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,1642,1668]" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Egg:</emphasis>
General color brown to dark brown. Slender, trilateral, with three longitudinal ridges (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1302,1641,1668]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,764,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-78@5.[151,1437,758,1440]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perlodinella kozlovi Klapálek, 1912 from Tianjun County, Qinghai, egg mass and single egg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810249" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810249/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="383">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Collar is a short brown ring, cylindrical with a broad base. Anchor mushroom-shaped with massive stem, evenly covered with small globular bodies. Each side of the egg with 3–6 short transverse rows of micropyles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
